13:42.333 --> 13:44.801
* Murder

13:44.801 --> 13:47.801
* Climb aboard
the murder train... *

13:48.801 --> 13:50.333
Lily.

13:50.333 --> 13:53.600
This is your masterpiece.

13:53.600 --> 13:55.600
We're getting a stakeout van!

13:55.600 --> 13:56.934
A station wagon?

13:56.934 --> 13:59.634
Really? You rented
a station wagon?

13:59.634 --> 14:01.500
Yeah, a van cost,
like, 25 bucks more.

14:01.500 --> 14:02.867
A station wagon?

14:05.567 --> 14:06.867
Greetings, Will Robinson!

14:06.867 --> 14:08.667
Where's the birthday
boy or girl?

14:08.667 --> 14:10.434
Hey, climb on in.

14:10.434 --> 14:11.567
What the hell is this?

14:11.567 --> 14:13.600
Oh, they didn't have
any stormtroopers,

14:13.600 --> 14:15.934
so I had to get a different
robot; this'll still work.

14:15.934 --> 14:17.200
Different robot?

14:17.200 --> 14:19.034
Stormtroopers
aren't robots.

14:19.034 --> 14:20.267
Of course
they're robots!

14:20.267 --> 14:22.500
"Must kill Luke Skywalker."

14:22.500 --> 14:24.534
<i>Um, nobody says that
in Star Wars at all, ever.</i>

14:24.534 --> 14:26.267
That's a really lousy
robot voice, honey.

14:26.267 --> 14:28.168
Someone order an
extra large sausage?

14:28.168 --> 14:31.134
Hey, one of Barney's videos
starts off just like that.

14:31.134 --> 14:33.934
Hey, guys, Barney's ordering...
five of something.

14:33.934 --> 14:35.300
I don't know if
it's gonna fit in here.

14:35.300 --> 14:37.600
Okay, now you're
just quoting the video.

14:37.600 --> 14:38.667
Still ordering.

14:38.667 --> 14:40.500
Waiter's taking out
a second pad.

14:40.500 --> 14:41.834
Yeah, okay, well,
we need it in here.

14:41.834 --> 14:42.867
We're on a stakeout.

14:42.867 --> 14:44.233
Shouldn't you be in a van?

14:44.233 --> 14:46.500
Thank you!
A van cost more.

14:46.500 --> 14:49.168
Score me a slice, Will Robinson!
No, no-no-no!

14:49.168 --> 14:50.800
You get a stain on that costume,
they're gonna charge us.

14:50.801 --> 14:52.301
Dude, will you just chill
about money?

14:52.500 --> 14:55.001
Yeah, let the stormtrooper
have a slice.

14:55.001 --> 14:57.101
BOTH:
It's not a stormtrooper!

14:57.101 --> 14:58.801
Hi, Lily

14:58.801 --> 15:00.934
Sorry I'm late.
I was looking for a van.

15:00.934 --> 15:02.834
Thank you!
$25!

15:02.834 --> 15:04.034
So should I go
say hi to Robin?

15:04.034 --> 15:05.134
Oh, not yet;
get in the car.

15:05.134 --> 15:07.267
Okay, so wait,
wait, wait.

15:07.267 --> 15:09.400
When they blew up
the Death Star,

15:09.400 --> 15:10.901
knowing full well
there were thousands

15:10.901 --> 15:13.400
of stormtroopers on it,
those were people?

15:13.400 --> 15:15.034
It was called
the Death Star, baby.

15:15.034 --> 15:17.034
They knew what
they were getting into.

15:17.034 --> 15:19.200
Look, I don't want to play
the "I'm Alan Thicke" card,

15:19.200 --> 15:21.534
but I really do have a dinner
to get to.

15:21.534 --> 15:23.233
Someone has got to
take this sausage!

15:23.733 --> 15:24.967
Okay, were you in that video?

15:24.967 --> 15:26.601
Were you the guy
with the farmer tan?

15:26.601 --> 15:29.000
Jonesin' for some 'za,
Will Robinson!

15:29.000 --> 15:30.634
Come on, I'm Alan Thicke!

15:30.635 --> 15:32.634
This ain't what I signed up for.

15:32.634 --> 15:35.367
Hey! That's what...
Hey, you know what? Everyone, stop!

15:35.367 --> 15:37.800
Alan Thicke, shut up! Marshall,
it's a station wagon.

15:37.800 --> 15:40.467
Get over it!
Ted, stop talking about porn!

15:40.467 --> 15:41.634
And for the love of God,

15:41.634 --> 15:43.568
somebody get the stormtrooper
some pizza!

15:43.568 --> 15:45.100
TED & MARSHALL:
It's not a stormtrooper!

15:45.100 --> 15:47.733
Crap!

15:47.733 --> 15:49.301
They see us!

15:49.302 --> 15:51.302
Danger! Danger!

15:57.134 --> 15:58.134
(whispers):
Are you sure they saw us?

15:58.134 --> 15:59.568
(whispers): Yes.
Hey!

15:59.568 --> 16:00.733
(screams)

16:00.733 --> 16:03.434
Can I go talk to Barney now?
I'm so excited!

16:03.434 --> 16:05.833
Do you really think
he's going to propose to me?

16:05.833 --> 16:07.367
Oh, honey...

16:07.367 --> 16:09.167
Forget it, Crazy Meg,
we've been made.

16:09.167 --> 16:10.634
If we try anything now,
they're going to know it's us.

16:10.634 --> 16:12.801
I, I think we should all just
go home...
No!

16:12.801 --> 16:14.767
This is my masterpiece.

16:14.767 --> 16:16.133
So what if they saw us?

16:16.133 --> 16:17.367
It'll still work.

16:17.367 --> 16:18.667
Stop it. We'll think
of something else.

16:18.667 --> 16:21.334
Let me repeat:
"I am Alan Thicke."

16:21.334 --> 16:23.801
(gasps):
You're Alan Thicke?!

16:23.801 --> 16:25.968
No.

16:25.968 --> 16:28.133
Alan Thicke, you're up.
Get on out there.

16:29.367 --> 16:31.334
<i>NARRATOR:
And so, Lily followed
through with her plan.</i>

16:31.334 --> 16:33.534
<i>First, Alan Thicke.</i>

16:34.634 --> 16:37.200
<i>Followed by Crazy Meg.</i>

16:37.200 --> 16:39.767
<i>Then, the robot.</i>

16:39.767 --> 16:42.567
<i>And finally, the dirty dishes.</i>

16:45.401 --> 16:46.900
<i>But by the end of it...</i>

16:47.934 --> 16:49.900
LILY:
They're kissing?

16:49.900 --> 16:51.334
They shouldn't be kissing!

16:51.334 --> 16:52.867
Why isn't this working?

16:52.867 --> 16:54.600
Because they're in love.

16:56.867 --> 16:58.767
It really was
just a rough patch.

16:58.767 --> 17:02.001
What the hell am I doing?

17:04.166 --> 17:06.601
This whole thing was a mistake.

17:07.434 --> 17:09.032
So, uh,

17:09.032 --> 17:11.133
any of you dudes
want to get high?

17:13.367 --> 17:15.467
I never thought I'd be
saying this tonight, but...

17:15.467 --> 17:17.534
to Barney and Robin,
the happy couple.

17:17.534 --> 17:18.867
(glasses clinking)

17:18.867 --> 17:20.367
<i>That was the moment we learned</i>

17:20.367 --> 17:21.701
<i>that relationships
take hard work,</i>

17:22.201 --> 17:24.567
<i>but eventually,
everything will work out.</i>

17:24.567 --> 17:26.532
Oh, hey!
Where's Barney?

17:26.532 --> 17:28.434
Uh, we broke up.

17:28.434 --> 17:31.001
<i>And that was the moment
we unlearned that other lesson</i>

17:31.001 --> 17:33.034
<i>we had just learned
a few seconds earlier.</i>

17:33.034 --> 17:35.500
<i>You see, earlier that night,
when Lily thought</i>

17:35.500 --> 17:37.567
<i>Barney and Robin
had spotted her,</i>

17:37.567 --> 17:39.334
<i>this is what they really saw.</i>

17:41.567 --> 17:45.334
Why do that fat guy
and old lady keep sta...?

17:47.134 --> 17:50.401
Oh, my God. That's us!

17:50.401 --> 17:52.533
Look at us.

17:52.533 --> 17:54.234
Did  always look this awful?

17:56.468 --> 17:58.301
Robin, I'm not happy.

17:58.301 --> 17:59.767
I mean,

17:59.767 --> 18:01.767
I wish I was.
Nothing would make me happier

18:01.767 --> 18:03.567
than being happy, but...

18:03.567 --> 18:05.201
I'm not.

18:06.201 --> 18:08.101
What are we doing wrong?

18:08.101 --> 18:09.267
We love each other.

18:09.267 --> 18:12.234
I mean, if this don't work,
what will?

18:12.234 --> 18:13.700
We're so similar.

18:13.700 --> 18:16.334
We both like scotch.
We're both awesome.

18:16.334 --> 18:18.101
You know, maybe that's it.

18:18.101 --> 18:20.201
Maybe there's just
too much awesome here.

18:20.201 --> 18:21.934
Exactly.

18:21.934 --> 18:24.234
Two awesomes
cancel each other out,

18:24.234 --> 18:27.900
and I'm tired of being
cancelled out.

18:27.900 --> 18:29.800
Me, too.

18:30.967 --> 18:33.234
Are we breaking up?

18:33.234 --> 18:35.301
I think so.

18:36.700 --> 18:39.101
Ah, crap.

18:39.101 --> 18:40.967
Now comes the next part.

18:40.967 --> 18:44.167
The part where you and can't
go back to being friends.

18:45.167 --> 18:49.468
Well, maybe this isn't
a breakup.

18:49.468 --> 18:52.967
Maybe this is two friends

18:52.967 --> 18:55.500
getting back together.

18:57.800 --> 18:59.800
ALAN THICKE: Robin!
Ooh!

18:59.800 --> 19:01.034
Alan...

19:01.034 --> 19:03.468
Oh, it's always so great
to see a fellow hoser.

19:03.468 --> 19:05.567
Yes! Oh, is true.
